	  programs still not running.

2014-11-17 15:23  bernlohr

	* common/fileopen.c (1.17): Conditional compilation for
	  glibc-specific line of code.

2014-11-14 20:47  bernlohr

	* corsika/io_simtel.c (1.25): CORSIKA header does not actually
	  contain how often a shower gets used.  So do not report this with
	  'read_hess -s' etc.

2014-11-14 16:37  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/eventio.c (1.43): Change the name of a variable
	  expf to avoid a compiler warning on some systems.

2014-10-28 15:23  bernlohr

	* hess/extract_hess.c (1.7): Increase the I/O buffer size and add
	  an option to adjust it further if needed.

2014-10-28 14:37  bernlohr

	* best_of.cc (1.12): Add an empty line for each gap in the energy
	  coverage.

2014-09-02 17:54  bernlohr

	* hess/: camera_image.c (1.30), io_hess.c (1.85), io_hess.h (1.83),
	  read_hess.c (1.109), reconstruct.c (1.55), reconstruct.h (1.21),
	  split_hessio.c (1.2): Add calibrated pixel intensities as an
	  optional representation instead of or in addition to raw data.
	  With a single gain channel per pixel it will never save space,
	  compared to summed raw data. Some space saving for two channels
	  per pixel. The new structure is allocated and filled only if
	  requested with the '--calibrate' option (or such data is
	  encountered on input).

2014-08-20 18:38  bernlohr

	* best_of.cc (1.11): Re-calculate the integral sensitivity
	  corresponding to the selected performance by re-summation of
	  event counts and applying Li&Ma etc.

2014-08-13 16:44  bernlohr

	* common/fileopen.c (1.16): Modify some messages for verbose
	  reporting of files opened and closed.

2014-08-04 15:05  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/: TestIO.cc (1.24), eventio.c (1.42), io_basic.h
	  (1.22), testio.c (1.22): Extend dynamic range of short floats by
	  using de-normalized numbers where necessary. Also include tests
	  of short floats into test programs.

2014-08-01 18:29  bernlohr

	* Makefile (1.109): Build the split_hessio program by default.

2014-08-01 18:28  bernlohr

	* best_of.cc (1.10): More flexibility in PPUT calculation for cases
	  where the sensitivity does not cover the full range as required.

2014-07-29 15:39  bernlohr

	* Makefile (1.108), Makefile.xxx (1.11), Makefile.xxx.depend (1.4),
	  hess/split_hessio.c (1.1): Add a tool which splits a sim_telarray
	  output file into - a file with run header material - a file with
	  run end material (typically just the histograms) - a file with
	  the true MC data - per telescope a file with config, setupand
	  calib data - per telescope a file with event data.  The latter
	  file can be in the original format (an 'Event' containing a
	  CentralEvent and a TelEvent and a TrackEvent) or the TelEvent
	  only unwrapped, or the raw data inside the TelEvent unwrapped.

