	* Makefile (1.93), build_test (1.1): Add automated build tests for
	  all common configurations.

2013-02-27 14:55  bernlohr

	* hess/read_hess.c (1.97): The remaining data block types from a
	  CORSIKA output file are also shown with 'read_hess -s'.

2013-02-27 14:32  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/eventio.c (1.33): Skipping an I/O block of length
	  zero could fail on input from a pipe.

2013-02-26 17:23  bernlohr

	* corsika/io_simtel.c (1.22), corsika/mc_tel.h (1.14),
	  hess/read_hess.c (1.96): Show a few more block types from CORSIKA
	  output with 'read_hess -s'.

2013-02-22 18:09  bernlohr

	* hess/io_hess.h (1.75): Rewrite definition of limits for different
	  CTA simulations.

2013-02-15 16:47  bernlohr

	* hess/read_hess.c (1.95): When reading multiple DST files make
	  sure that the configuration parameter histogram 99 is never added
	  up.

2013-02-13 17:19  bernlohr

	* hess/: io_hess.c (1.74), io_hess.h (1.74), read_hess.c (1.94):
	  The data format had problems when more than 32k pixels or sectors
	  were used. Fixing the data format, using the new version only
	  when needed. When pixel and sector numbers fit into 16-bit int,
	  we continue to use the old format. Also adding a few more print
	  statements for 'read_hess -s'.

2013-02-13 16:52  bernlohr

	* eventio_addon/io_histogram.c (1.19): Fix compiler warning

2013-02-13 16:50  bernlohr

	* Makefile (1.92), Makefile.xxx (1.3), Makefile.xxx.depend (1.1),
	  best_of.cc (1.6): Proper dependencies for hessioxxx package

2013-02-13 15:22  bernlohr

	* hess/io_hess.h (1.73): Add configuration variant with a huge
	  number of pixels for a few telescopes.  Unfortunately, the linker
	  comes with relocation errors when using more than some 200+x
	  thousand pixels.

2013-02-11 19:42  bernlohr

	* Makefile (1.91), Makefile.xxx (1.2), list_histograms.c (1.1),
	  common/histogram.c (1.18), eventio_addon/io_histogram.c (1.18):
	  Fix histogram listings for histograms with more than 2^31-1
	  entries (alhough format still limited to 2^32-1).  Adding a
	  utility program to list histograms without dependency on PAW
	  (CERNLIB) or ROOT.

