2010-11-17 17:58  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/EventIO.hh (1.38): Fix recently introduced
	  compilation problem on 64-bit systems.

2010-11-17 14:17  bernlohr

	* hess/rec_tools.c (1.14): Share rec_tools with sim_telarray.

2010-11-15 16:50  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/: EventIO.hh (1.37), TestIO.cc (1.21), testio.c
	  (1.19): Include specific test cases for count32 and scount32
	  elements.

2010-11-15 16:48  bernlohr

	* hess/: io_hess.c (1.58), io_hess.h (1.55): Changing data format
	  for (F)ADC raw data to use scount32 instead of uint16 for ADC
	  sums, allowing for sums exceeding 64K and at the same time saving
	  10% space after compression for the more typical cases. Similarly
	  the sample mode data is now stored as scount16, again saving disk
	  space and allowing for extension to more than 16-bit ADCs.

2010-11-15 16:35  bernlohr

	* hess/: rec_tools.c (1.13), rec_tools_nr.c (1.4): More accurate
	  transformation at large off-axis angles.

2010-11-03 18:48  bernlohr

	* fcat.c (1.2): Write include such that it also works after a fresh
	  check-out.

2010-10-22 13:20  bernlohr

	* hess/camera_image.c (1.21): Change bounding box of PS page to
	  standard A4.

2010-09-09 00:55  bernlohr

	* hess/: camera_image.c (1.20), reconstruct.c (1.39), reconstruct.h
	  (1.16): Shifting the pixel shape guessing function to avoid
	  introducing additional dependencies for read_hess_nr.

2010-09-09 00:32  bernlohr

	* hess/: camera_image.c (1.19), reconstruct.c (1.38), reconstruct.h
	  (1.15): For camera image produced with read_hess, we have to
	  guess the pixel shape based on the direction of displacements
	  between neighbour pixels.

