	  smaller diameters in the reconstruction in a type-specific way.

2009-01-30 17:48  bernlohr

	* hess/read_hess.c (1.62): Allow reading the list of input file
	  names from a file since there are still systems around with
	  rather strict limits on the maximum length of the command line
	  (like Linux before kernel 2.6.23) and/or the maximum number of
	  command line arguments (POSIX only requires 4096).

2009-01-30 17:09  bernlohr

	* common/fileopen.c (1.7): Also read files from remote SSH servers
	  (ssh://user@host:file syntax).

2009-01-29 14:36  bernlohr

	* hbook/cvt2.c (1.16), root/cvt3.cc (1.13): When too many
	  histograms are available to fit onto the command line, you can
	  pass them by standard input, as in "find -name 'gamma*.hdata.gz |
	  hdata2hbook -A -o gamma.hbook"

