	* hess/: io_hess.c (1.42), io_hess.h (1.42), read_hess.c (1.58),
	  reconstruct.c (1.25), reconstruct.h (1.9): Including pixel timing
	  results together with Hillas parameters etc. into the DST-level
	  data.

2008-10-06 13:48  bernlohr

	* corsika/: io_simtel.c (1.9), mc_tel.h (1.7): Optional mode where
	  photon bunch data is not written in one block for a whole array
	  but in blocks for individual telescopes (enclosed by a header and
	  trailer block). This can save memory for large arrays but chances
	  of getting incomplete data will rise, and overhead in sequential
	  mode will be more severe.

2008-09-12 20:54  bernlohr

	* hess/: io_hess.c (1.41), read_hess.c (1.57), read_hess_nr.c
	  (1.2): Take care of telescope IDs above 255 in a number of data
	  block types.

2008-08-13 17:56  bernlohr

	* hess/io_hess.h (1.41): Fix little typo.

2008-08-13 13:54  bernlohr

	* hess/io_hess.h (1.40): Enlarge maximum number of telescopes for
	  really big CTA simulations when compiled with -DCTA_ULTRA.

2008-07-07 19:41  bernlohr

	* hess/rec_tools_nr.c (1.1): Add stripped-down version of
	  rec_tools.c as rec_tools_nr.c.

2008-06-11 14:29  bernlohr

	* Makefile (1.74): In old versions of the Makefile, the binaries
	  were built in the module's top level directory and these were not
	  removed by 'make clean' of a newer Makefile. Remove them each
	  time. Use symlinks to the bin directory if you need them in the
	  top level.

2008-06-06 14:12  bernlohr

	* Makefile (1.73): Improve handling of bin, lib, out, ... when they
	  exist as symbolic links.

