	* hess/: camera_image.c (1.12), io_hess.c (1.33), io_hess.h (1.35):
	  Optional 'CTA' instead of 'H.E.S.S.' on camera images.  Add
	  printing of tracking data.

2008-01-16 13:37  bernlohr

	* Makefile (1.70), hbook/Makefile (1.16): Using now gfortran (if
	  available) as the FORTRAN compiler for the HBOOK interface. Note
	  that this requires a compatible CERNLIB (i.e. compiled with
	  gfortran) to work. If it doesn't work you are not loosing much,
	  since building the hdata2hbook program is optional.

2008-01-11 17:03  bernlohr

	* corsika/io_simtel.c (1.8): Use fileopen/fileclose instead of
	  explicitly opening large files with fopen64.	Optionally check
	  the sum of photon bunches, taking into account that with the
	  EXTENDED_TELOUT option to CORSIKA/IACT there are 'bunches' that
	  refer to the emitting particles and not to the photons emitted.

