	  root/cvt3.cc (1.9): Better input name to output name translation
	  for compressed input files.

2004-01-12 15:08  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/: EventIO.cc (1.7), EventIO.hh (1.11), TestIO.cc
	  (1.8), testio.c (1.9): Added functions for vectors and valarrays
	  of bools. The C language test program writes and reads identical
	  data packed in bytes.

2004-01-11 19:55  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/: EventIO.cc (1.6), EventIO.hh (1.10): Optionally
	  throwing exceptions on some problems that are usually due to bad
	  usage.

2003-12-08 20:22  bernlohr

	* hbook/Makefile (1.9), root/Makefile (1.3), root/toroot.cc (1.4):
	  Take more care here which version of the library to link with,
	  even when it makes no practical difference since CONFIG_ITEM
	  (where it matters) is not used in the hdata2hbook and hdata2root
	  converters.

2003-12-07 18:35  bernlohr

	* Makefile (1.43), common/initial.h (1.5), doc_src/eventio_de.tex
	  (1.4), doc_src/eventio_en.tex (1.4), eventio_basic/EventIO.cc
	  (1.5), eventio_basic/EventIO.hh (1.9), eventio_basic/TestIO.cc
	  (1.7), eventio_basic/eventio.c (1.13), eventio_basic/io_basic.h
	  (1.6), eventio_basic/testio.c (1.8): Implementation of Count type
	  variables extended to support 64-bit numbers. A new basic type
	  SCount was added which is a signed number complement to the Count
	  variables. An SCount between -63 and 63 requires one byte of
	  storage, other SCounts between -8191 and 8191 need 2 bytes and so
	  on.

2003-11-19 20:10  bernlohr

	* hess/: io_hess.c (1.20), io_hess.h (1.21): Add the area weight
	  needed for importance sampling also to the sim_hessarray output
	  in a format that is compatible with older software, where
	  possible.

2003-11-12 20:22  bernlohr

	* corsika/: io_simtel.c (1.6), mc_tel.h (1.5): Preparing data
	  format in back- and forward-compatible way for a possible
	  importance sampling of core positions.

2003-11-12 20:21  bernlohr

	* hess/: camera_image.c (1.10), read_hess.c (1.16), reconstruct.c
	  (1.8): When reconstructing the images again, plot these images
	  and not the original ones.

