	  tools.

2002-04-26 22:17  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/eventio.c (1.6): A potential problem with lseek
	  fixed (relevant only when compiling with -D_FILE_OFFSETBITS=64
	  and at the same time without -D_LARGEFILE64_SOURCE on 32-bit
	  glibc systems (like Linux x86). A few other places, where the
	  compiler (with every possible warning turned on) might warn, have
	  been commented as expected and irrelevant warnings.

2002-04-25 19:23  bernlohr

	* eventio_basic/listio.c (1.5): 'listio -s' should now work with
	  data blocks up to 128 MB.

